		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; <date>Sunday&#44; 29th Sivan &#40;<del>May</del> June&#41;&#44; 1851</date></p>
			<p>To my friend the wise&#44; etc.&#44; etc&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">That which I sent you&#44; you can advertise in the <date>August</date><lb/> number. On the subscription list to your Bible you can also<lb/> put my name. I am now too far away from Jews to be able<lb/> work among them for this purpose. Since I resigned my<lb/> Rabbinate&#44; I have very little to do with Jews. I quietly<lb/> look on at your quarrel with <persName>Dr. Wise</persName>&#44; may his name rot<lb/> moreover&#44; I am convinced that nothing good can come of it. For<lb/> our sages have said that one must not dispute with Jewish<lb/> heretics and yet when we think we have more wisdom than the<lb/> sages of the Talmud&#44; it can come to no good. That is why<lb/> I say about you what the wise man said to the Kusari&#44;<lb/> &#34;The intention is acceptable&#44; but the deeds are not. However<lb/> you can do what you please while I remain a quiet<lb/> onlooker.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Your devoted friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Abraham Rice</persName>.</p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
